column111:
for some time now the farmers in our community and the fulani cattle rearers had a common understanding on land use. it was such that during the rainy season, the cattle rearers leave thereby allowing the farmers the convenience of cultivating their farms. after the harvest is done,the cattle rearers return to graze their cattle.
 however in recent times, the fulani cattle rearers refused to keep to the agreement. rather, they chose to dwell in our community all year round thereby disrupting and destroying our farming activities. this led to violent clashes
